<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>CF 500, CF 600 Driveshaft - Driveshaft - Disassembly and Assembly</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="disassemble" graphiccount="15">
        <title>Disassembly and Assembly</title>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Center Bearing</title>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para>Do not clamp the driveshaft in the jaws of a vise or a similar holding fixture.</para>
                </caution>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Place the driveshaft on a suitable workbench.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">On reverse slip driveshafts, while using a suitable flange holding tool to prevent shaft
                    rotation, remove the driveshaft flange nut.
                </para>
                <para>&#8226; To install, tighten to 407 Nm (300 lb-ft).</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0501019" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figde2/de2437a.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="232px"/>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">On reverse slip driveshafts, remove the flange.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0501020" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figde0/de0872a.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="232px"/>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the driveshaft slip yoke and the slip yoke boot.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the rubber insulator surrounding the bearing.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0501021" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../fign00/n0020377.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="232px"/>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Remove the driveshaft center bearing retainer.</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Remove the driveshaft center bearing bracket.</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Remove the rubber insulator.</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Using a suitable press, remove the bearing from the driveshaft.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0501022" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figE92/E9282A.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="232px"/>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Using a suitable press, remove the dust slinger.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0501023" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figE92/E9283A.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="232px"/>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Clean grease deposits, dirt and rust from the stub shaft.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Inspect the stub shaft splines for nicks, gouges or burrs. Remove with a file or emery
                        cloth.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>The driveshaft center bearing bracket must be installed with the deep flange rearward.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">To assemble, reverse the disassembly procedure.</para>
                <randlist type="bullet">
                    <item>
                        <para>Lubricate the stub shaft spline with grease.</para>
                        <randlist type="dash">
                            <item>
                                <para>Use Premium Long-Life Grease XG-1-C or equivalent</para>
                            </item>
                        </randlist>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <para>Install new driveshaft slip yoke boot clamps.</para>
                    </item>
                </randlist>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Driveshaft Universal Joint - Single Cardan, Flange Yoke Disassembly</title>
            <table id="t0501005">
                <title>Special Tool</title>
                <tgroup cols="2">
                    <colspec colname="col1" colwidth="1.16*"/>
                    <colspec colname="col2" colwidth="0.84*"/>
                    <tbody>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <graphic filename="../figST1/ST1172A.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="152px"
                                         scalefitheight="112px"/>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Installer/Remover, C-Frame and Screw</para>
                                <para>OTC 7248</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
            <para>
                <emph type="bold">Initial Disassembly</emph>
            </para>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para>Do not, under any circumstance, clamp the driveshaft in the jaws of a vise or similar holding
                        fixture. Denting or localizing fracture can result, causing driveshaft failure during vehicle
                        operation.
                    </para>
                </caution>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Place the driveshaft on a suitable workbench. Do not damage the tube.</para>
            </step1>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>If components are not marked and installed incorrectly, driveline imbalance can occur.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Index-mark the driveshaft components.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0501024" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figGE0/GE0293a.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="232px"/>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove and discard all 4 of the snap rings.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0501025" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figGE0/GE0295a.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="232px"/>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Clamp the special tool in a vise.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0501026" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../fign00/n0020382.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="232px"/>
            </figure>
            <para>
                <emph type="bold">Bearing Cup Removal</emph>
            </para>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>If necessary, use a pair of pliers to remove a bearing cup that fails to press out all the
                        way.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the bearing cups and the flange.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0501027" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../fign00/n0020383.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="232px"/>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Position the flange in the special tool.</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Press out a bearing cup.</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Rotate the flange 180 degrees.</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Press on the spider to remove the remaining bearing cup.</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Remove the flange.</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <para>
                <emph type="bold">Final Disassembly</emph>
            </para>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Repeat bearing cup removal in this procedure to remove the remaining bearing cups and
                    the spider from the driveshaft.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0501028" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figA00/A0026322.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="232px"/>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Clean the yoke area at the end of the driveshaft.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Driveshaft Universal Joint - Single Cardan, Flange Yoke Assembly</title>
            <para>
                <emph type="bold">Bearing Cup Installation</emph>
            </para>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Install the Universal Joint Kits as complete assemblies only. Do not mix components from other
                        kits.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install a new spider and bearing cups.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0501029" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../fign00/n0020385.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="232px"/>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Start a new bearing cup in the driveshaft yoke.
                        <callout2 type="alpha">Check the needle bearings for correct positioning.</callout2>
                    </callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Position the new spider in the driveshaft yoke.</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Position the driveshaft yoke in the special tool.</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Press the bearing cup to just below the snap ring groove.
                        <callout2 type="alpha">Repeat to install the new bearing cup on the opposite side of the
                            driveshaft yoke.
                        </callout2>
                    </callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <para>
                <emph type="bold">Flange Installation</emph>
            </para>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Inspect the flange. Install a new flange, if necessary.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the new bearing cups and the flange.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0501030" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../fign00/n0020386.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="232px"/>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Start a new bearing cup in the flange.
                        <callout2 type="alpha">Check the needle bearings for correct positioning.</callout2>
                    </callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Position the flange on the spider.</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Position the assembly in the special tool.</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Press the bearing cup to just below the snap ring groove.
                        <callout2 type="alpha">Repeat to install the new bearing cup on the opposite side of the
                            flange.
                        </callout2>
                    </callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <para>
                <emph type="bold">Final Assembly</emph>
            </para>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Use the yellow snap rings supplied in the kit to assemble the universal joint (U-joint). If
                        difficulty is encountered with the yellow snap rings, install the black snap rings.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the driveshaft from the special tool, and install the 4 new snap rings.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0501031" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figGE0/GE0298A.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="232px"/>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para>Do not strike the bearings.</para>
                </caution>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Check the U-joint for freedom of movement.</para>
                <para>&#8226; If binding, strike the yoke with a brass or plastic hammer.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0501032" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figGE0/GE0299A.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="232px"/>
            </figure>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
